# User-facing yoink output. In dev mode the server's Desktop resolves to
# the user's actual Desktop -- and on this machine the OneDrive Desktop
# IS the directory the repo lives in, so topic folders land at the repo
# root. Ignore them explicitly. New topics added to topics.json need a
# new line here. Future-proof with /Yoink-Output/ for an eventual
# explicit-output-dir refactor.
_sessions/
_all-yoinks-index.md
_yoink-trash/
/Yoink-Output/

# Topic folders (one per entry in topics.json + the Uncategorized
# fallback). On Windows NTFS git uses core.ignorecase=true, so a generic
# `/[A-Z]*/` glob would also match docs/ and extension/ -- list each one
# explicitly instead.
/AI and ML/
/Developer Marketing/
/Job Hunt and Career/
/New Tools to Try/
/Productivity and Workflows/
/Social Media Research/
/Uncategorized/

# Private launch copy drafts. Keep these local unless deliberately published.
docs/launch/

.claude/

# Dev-mode parallel-AI worktrees. These belong as sibling directories
# (..\Yoink-claude-v2 and ..\Yoink-codex-v2) so git worktree commands
# work correctly. If they end up nested inside the main repo (as can
# happen when moved by hand), keep them out of commits. Recreate them
# as siblings with `git worktree add` when needed for a new sprint.
/Yoink-claude-v2/
/Yoink-codex-v2/
